    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-01-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-01-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="782"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d782">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 882.51/641.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Messrs. <gloss type="from">Kuhn, Loeb and Company</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-01-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 21, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>We have the honor to acknowledge receipt of your telegram and we have again
                    communicated with the National City Bank, the fiscal agents for the Liberian
                    loan, who inform us that they have taken up this question with their attorneys,
                    Messrs. Sherman and Sterling, who will communicate direct with your
                    Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Kuhn, Loeb and Company.</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
